rComments: Shes a decent prof, dont bother going to class tho, everything you need is in the textbook. Project was easy but marked harder than expected. Midterm was easy, final exam was a bit more difficult, make sure you do all the required readings if you want a good grade.

She's a phenomenal professor, honestly one of the best ones I've had in my university career so far. Her lectures are stimulating and her expectations of the course is clear. You WILL need a textbook if you want to do well in this class though, not having one will be detrimental.  All in all, go to her lectures and read the textbook, easy A.

She's the best prof to take this class with. The midterm was super easy common sense type questions. The final exam you need to study more and read the textbook + articles. Assignment marking can be a bit anal, but there are literally 2 chapters in the textbook that teach you how to do it. Follow it and you'll do fine.

Jenn's class was super fun and informative. Her stories about her experience in the health care system helped me better understand the lecture materials. The midterm and exam are easy A's if you study and read the textbook. The assignment was decent too.  She's the best prof to take HSS comm with!

Honestly the easiest HSS class you'll ever take. Midterm and exam requires minimal effort, just read the PPT + textbook. The written assignment is a little bit trickier, but just follow the rubric religiously and you should be fine. 10/10 would recommend. Also BUY THE TEXTBOOK

The lectures consisted of her reading the slides with random personal stories thrown in, making it difficult to attend class. The readings were long and unnecessary as they didn't add anything to the course except extra work. Her idea of marking consisted of obscure comments with no rubric as reference. TL;DR: There are better electives out there.

One of the best profs I've ever had, she is very sweet and try cares for her students. She tries to use real-life examples for the content being taught and tries to make us understand past just memorizing and knowing enough to pass. Exams are very fair, however final was a bit harder as focused more on readings. Assignment was also very entertainig
